Privacy Policy: BP Health App Usage
This Privacy Policy describes Our policies and procedures on the collection, use and disclosure of Your information when You use the Service and tells You about Your privacy rights and how the law protects You.
We use Your Personal data to provide and improve the Service. By using the Service, you agree to the collection and use of information in accordance with this Privacy Policy.
Terms and Conditions
This guideline will explain how BP Health App will collect, use and store your personal information. We will use this Privacy Policy to explain the relevant details, including the following:
We will describe the types of personal information we collect and their corresponding use in order for you to understand how we collect specific type of personal information for a particular function, the reasons for its use and the methods of such collection.
While using some features, we will collect your personal information after obtaining your consent. Unless it is required by the relevant laws and regulations for you to provide such information, refusing to provide such information will only result in you're not being able to use the specific functions relating to such information, but does not affect your normal use of other functions of BP Health App.
At present, BP Health App will not actively obtain your personal information from a third party. If there is a requirement to obtain your personal information indirectly from a third party for future business development purposes, we will clarify with you the source, type and scope of such personal information. For example, if the specific development is beyond the scope of what you originally agreed to provide to a third party, we will obtain your prior express consent before processing your personal information, and we will strictly abide by the relevant laws and regulations and require that the third party guarantees the legitimacy of the information provided.
As you engage with BP Health App, we gather information provided by you during your use of the service and information generated through your interactions. This enables us to deliver our services effectively, optimize your experience, and safeguard your account
Information You Provide
When you input data, give feedback, or participate in online activities, we collect pertinent personal information required for those activities. This data helps us meet your requests, provide relevant products/services, and counteract fraudulent activities.
Information We Obtain
To enhance your usage experience, we may gather and employ your relevant information. This includes data such as API/JS code version, browser, IP address, platform, timestamp, application details, device identifiers, and more. This information assists us in tailoring our services and maintaining their quality.
Within the framework of applicable laws and regulations or user agreements, we employ collected data as follows. If we employ your information beyond these purposes, we will clarify the reasons and seek your consent:
Service Provision
Your personal data enables us to deliver and support our services. This encompasses sending service announcements, technical notifications, updates, security alerts, and support-related messages through the service or via email. We also address your support queries and feedback.
Personalization
We use collected information for internal analysis and research, resulting in more accurate and personalized services and content.
Product Development and Enhancement
Information aids our understanding of your interests and the service, facilitating improvements and the creation of new features. In the event of system malfunctions, we may analyze crash-generated data to optimize our services.
Security Assurance
Your information contributes to identity authentication, safety measures, anti-fraud monitoring, storage, backup, customer safety services, and more.
Push Notifications
We may send emails, text messages, news, or push notifications while you use our services. You can unsubscribe from these via relevant notices on your device.
Interest-Based Recommendations
We may recommend ads, news, and content that align with your preferences.
Effectiveness Evaluation
Information may be used to assess and enhance the impact of ads and promotions within our services.
Sharing
Your personal data is shared solely with BP Health App, except in the following instances:
With your explicit consent, we share your personal data.
As required by laws or government mandates, we may share information.
We share necessary data with affiliates, aligned with this Privacy Policy's objectives.
Authorized partners may access data to improve services, subject to privacy and security requirements.
Transfer
Transfers only occur:
With your explicit consent.
During mergers or acquisitions, new entities must comply with this policy.
Public Disclosure
Your information is publicly disclosed only:
With your explicit consent.
When legally required.
Storage
We store personal data within China's jurisdiction as per laws and regulations.
Retention
Data is retained for the necessary time to fulfill purposes outlined in this policy or to comply with regulations. Deactivation prompts data deletion.
Security
Industry-standard measures protect your data. While we strive to secure your information, its absolute safety can't be guaranteed. Contact us immediately in case of security concerns.
Access and Modification
You can access your account, amend settings, and manage your data in BP Health App.
Withdraw Consent
Change your consent preferences in system settings. Past consent-based data processing remains unaffected.
Response to Requests
For security, we may verify your identity before allowing access, modification, or deletion.
Minors under 18 require parental consent to use BP Health App, as per relevant laws and regulations.
We reserve the right to update this privacy policy at any time. We will notify you of any changes by posting the new Privacy Policy on this page.
This policy is effective as of 2023-09-20
If you have any questions about the Policy or this Agreement, or if you would like to obtain a previous version of the current document, feel free to contact us at
